// A `task:Scheduler` can be used to create timers to trigger periodically. A
// service can be attached to the task scheduler object using the `attach()`
// method and the listener can be started using the `start()` method.
// The service that is being attached must contain the `onTrigger()` resource function.
// Additionally, a user can pass a set of `any` values to the resource using
// the [`attach()`](https://ballerina.io/swan-lake/learn/api-docs/ballerina/#/task/classes/Scheduler#attach) method, which then can be used inside the `onTrigger()`
// function. The Listener can be stopped by calling the `stop()` method.<br/><br/>
// For more information on the underlying module, 
// see the [Task module](https://ballerina.io/swan-lake/learn/api-docs/ballerina/#/task/).
